Interestingly , both <p1  pair=10 >  <prot>  GRB2 </prot>  </p1>  and <p1  pair=11 >  <prot>  phosphatidylinositol - 3 ( PI - 3 ) kinase </prot>  </p1>  can simultaneously bind distinct tyrosine phosphorylated regions on the same <p2  pair=10 >  <p2  pair=11 >  <prot>  IRS - 1 </prot>  </p2>  </p2>  molecule , suggesting a mechanism whereby <prot>  IRS - 1 </prot>  could provide the core for a large signalling complex .
